editorialSummary.text: DJs & bottle service keep the party going at this bi-level club with a high-wattage sound system.

originalText.text: I came here for a private event, so can't speak for the other reviews. I found the bouncers, staff and bartenders attentive. The space itself is nice with plenty of private table seating and spacious floor.

originalText.text: I arrived at the establishment around 1:30 or 2 AM, and the doorman informed me that they were closing and couldn't allow anyone else in. While waiting for my Uber, I noticed that the doorman let in other individuals who arrived after me, which felt unfair. It's disappointing to feel discriminated against based on race. I hope the establishment addresses these issues to ensure a welcoming environment for all patrons.

originalText.text:
How is this place still operating? The way they extort money & discriminate against their patrons is beyond disgusting. They denied my group of guy friends entry because they had no females entering with them & basically stated that "the only way for you to get in, is to get a bottle and table, which is going to be $600." Are you kidding me? Not only do they force you to get a table, they force EVERY FEMALE to check in their sweater, jacket, coat, etc, while every guy is still wearing their hoodie, sweatshirt, jacket. You have absolutely no say in the matter. Lastly, the bartenders have such a superiority complex about them and are just plain rude. To the male & female bartender working on 9/29, you really need to check your attitude, especially if you work in the service industry.

Do yourself a favor & don't waste your time at this trashy place. Vibes, music, & workers are all garbage. Negative 5 stars.
